s=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104izj1665702893142.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/izj1665702893142.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/izj1665702893142.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"izj1665702893142\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface as a DDE Server\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"izj1665702893142__uniface_as_a_dde_server_114495\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When Uniface acts as a DDE server, the DDE link must be defined in the client application.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"izj1665702893142__p_d35669e1_d35670e1_d35671e1\">When you next select the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Paste Link</span> command in a program that can act as a DDE client, a DDE link is established. After that, whenever the linked data changes in Uniface, it changes in the client application. For example, if the client is a worksheet application with a link to Uniface, the worksheet app attempts to refresh the linked data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"izj1665702893142__p_d35672e1_d35673e1_d35674e1\">The client application can only obtain data from Uniface when it is running and the referenced component is current. If Uniface is not running, the client application may offer to start it. Unfortunately, it cannot run the correct component automatically.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"izj1665702893142__p_d35675e1_d35676e1_d35677e1\">Only the <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"<var class=\"keyword varname\">field.entity</var>\"</code> item syntax is supported for poke transactions. Poke transactions cannot operate on fields that have focus.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"izj1665702893142__p_d35678e1_d35679e1_d35680e1\">Execute transactions result in the receiveMessage trigger being fired. The command string is available in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wgz1719591021043.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>DDE Syntax Rules</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kff1719927936500.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Programmed Links</a><p>If you want to define links with multiple fields or even multiple occurrences, you must use a programmed link. This is because it is not possible to select more than one field in Uniface for copying to the Microsoft Windows clipboard.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fkg1719680200265.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>DDE Links</a><p>Applications that communiicate via DDE do so using links that can be defined by copying and pasting them to the destination application or programming them using the DDE syntax rules.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528767\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528767\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface as a DDE Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface as a DDE Server When Uniface acts as a DDE server, the DDE link must be defined in the client application. When you next select the Paste Link command in a program that can act as a DDE client, a DDE link is established. After that, whenever the linked data changes in Uniface, it changes in the client application. For example, if the client is a worksheet application with a link to Uniface, the worksheet app attempts to refresh the linked data. The client application can only obtain data from Uniface when it is running and the referenced component is current. If Uniface is not running, the client application may offer to start it. Unfortunately, it cannot run the correct component automatically. Only the \" field.entity \" item syntax is supported for poke transactions. Poke transactions cannot operate on fields that have focus. Execute transactions result in the receiveMessage trigger being fired. The command string is available in $result . Related Links DDE Syntax Rules Programmed Links If you want to define links with multiple fields or even multiple occurrences, you must use a programmed link. This is because it is not possible to select more than one field in Uniface for copying to the Microsoft Windows clipboard. DDE Links Applications that communiicate via DDE do so using links that can be defined by copying and pasting them to the destination application or programming them using the DDE syntax rules. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}